<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Return on Investments: Comparing APY and APR</h3>



<p>Comparing the Annual Percentage Yield (APY) and Annual Percentage Rate (APR) provides valuable insights into the potential returns on investments in Polygon&#8217;s liquidity pools.</p>



<p>APY takes compounding into account and is generally higher than APR, making it a more accurate reflection of the actual return. When evaluating potential returns, it&#8217;s crucial to consider the frequency of compounding and any fees associated with the liquidity pool.</p>



<p>While APR indicates the simple interest rate, APY reflects the effective annualized interest rate when compounding is factored in.</p>



