<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How Staking Supports Governance and Security on the Network</h3>



<p>Staking involves the act of locking up funds in a cryptocurrency wallet to support the operations of a blockchain network.</p>



<p>In the case of Polygon, staking not only helps secure the network but also supports governance by allowing token holders to participate in decision-making processes. Through staking, token holders can vote on proposals and changes to the network, thereby influencing its direction and development.</p>



<p>Additionally, stakers are incentivized to act in the network&#8217;s best interest through rewards, aligning their incentives with the overall security and stability of the ecosystem.</p>



<p>This interconnected relationship between staking, governance, and security is essential for the efficient functioning and sustainability of the Polygon network.</p>



